11/12/2009
NICOSIA, Cyprus -- Police announced on Friday (December 11th) that the body of former President Tassos Papadopoulos has been taken from his grave at the Deftera cemetery, on the outskirts of Nicosia. Thieves stole the corpse late Thursday night or early Friday morning, investigators said. Papadopoulos died of lung cancer on December 12th 2008 at the age of 74. (AP, BBC, AFP, DPA - 11/12/09)
